predictions.text: Central cardiovascular effects of AVP and ANP

Patients with hypercalcemia resulting from medical diseases and bipolar patients with lithium-associated hypercalcemia had significantly higher frequencies of conduction defects. Patients in group A had significant mortality at 2-year follow-up (28%)
in contrast to zero mortality in the other three groups.
Syndrome of inappropriate secretion of antidiuretic hormone
